      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must be under version-controlled QA process with documented test suite covering relevant flow regimes.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2021R2 is deployed under an ISO 9001-compliant QA framework. Regression test suite covers turbulent pipe flow, rotating machinery, and hemolysis benchmark cases. Version control and audit trail are maintained throughout the simulation campaign."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations via method-of-manufactured-solutions or equivalent benchmark comparison.",
      "rationale": "Code verification performed against the FDA critical path benchmark pump dataset. Pressure-flow curves and velocity profiles match published experimental data within 5% across all five operating points. MMS verification for the SST k-omega turbulence model is documented in the solver validation report."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be below 5% for the primary hemolysis quantity of interest.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh refinement study performed at 3M, 9M, and 24M cells. GCI for the scalar stress-weighted hemolysis index is 2.1% between the medium and fine meshes. The medium mesh (9M cells) is selected for the production runs as it achieves the required accuracy within acceptable computational cost."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions used for validation must be documented and traceable to the physical test setup.",
      "rationale": "Inlet flow rates and rotational speeds for the five operating points are taken directly from the FDA critical path pump experimental protocol. Temperature, fluid viscosity, and hematocrit are recorded and applied as boundary conditions in the CFD model."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) must agree with experimental measurements within the stated uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Predicted RH values at all five operating points fall within the experimental uncertainty envelope (±15%). The model correctly ranks operating points by hemolysis severity, confirming its suitability for worst-case identification."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI (relative hemolysis index) must be directly linked to the clinical endpoint and regulatory acceptance criterion.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the established regulatory metric for pump-induced hemolysis assessment per ISO 10993-4 and FDA guidance. Its direct relationship to erythrocyte damage makes it appropriate for the COU decision."
    },
    {
